<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Chicken Note</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="edn297">  297  By introducing his sister to his proxy, Shaun mimics Christ. Cf. St. John l9. 25-27: &lsquo;Now there stood by the cross of Jesus his mother and his mother's sister [Christ's &lsquo;aunt&rsquo;], Mary the wife of Cleophas, and Mary Magdalene. When Jesus therefore saw his mother, and the disciple standing by, whom he loved, he saith unto his mother, Woman behold thy son! Then saith he to the disciple, Behold thy mother! And from that hour the disciple took her unto his own home.&rsquo;  </div>
